it’s all about your marketable worth

convos usually go like this:

-_What is your expected salary?_
- I am more interested in finding out if we are a good fit for each other first and then we can talk about the salary.
- _But surely you have a range in what you are looking for?_
- I believe that a salary is measured as a salary package meaning that it is a complicated matter of salary + benefits. What are the company benefits?
- _What is your target salary though?_
- I have hired people before and I know that the best person that knows the compensation number is the hiring manager because he evaluates how much value a person can bring to the company. What is your budget range for this position?
"I can earn 200k a year in silicon valley, just so you know. I’d pay 400k a year for a studio apartment and starbucks coffees, but that doesn’t matter"

so that means wherever you live you should be getting what you worth in market (which market we will be referring here)
if they ask me for something lower (without giving me their number) then I say all the skills I have and what that brings to them. Basically I am forcing them to give me their number
